{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dc58ccf7-c3f7-4fc7-bdfd-bcb67342422d","content":"Yes, you **will** run into compatibility issues. MSTest v3 dropped support for two of your three target frameworks:\n\n| Framework | MSTest v3 Support |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Dropped — minimum is `net6.0` |\n| `net462` | ❌ Dropped — minimum is `net462` → actually **net462 is OK** (minimum is .NET Framework 4.6.2) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Dropped — minimum is `net6.0` |\n\n**Summary of issues:**\n\n1. **`net5.0`** — not supported. You must upgrade to `net6.0` or later.\n2. **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported. You must upgrade to `net6.0` or later.\n3. **`net462`** — this one is fine; MSTest v3 still supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+.\n\n**Before migrating**, update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net6.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nWould you like me to perform the full migration (update TFMs + upgrade to MSTest v3)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0d62e3fa-383f-43a3-baf5-323f1dba1bbe","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"8430:675B2:511CDFB:5D4E139:6A0AD9A4"},"id":"c04eda2d-c28c-41ee-a418-37828d906cb8","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:19:41.007Z","parentId":"c3d000e3-1081-4167-8a93-f6a6de27fdc2"}
